<br>
In case you wonder, no, I did not just fall off a turnip truck. I just don't like LDoN so wouldn't even look at the rewards. I can't be too far behind the curve as I've not seen a whole lot casting of this.<br>
<br>
&quot;Death by AoE&quot; is by far my most common problem on raids. A 1600hps spell damage shield would be handy. Then again, I suppose I could just work on my resists to what I was supposed to have 50 levels ago. Peridots and LDoN &gt; Resist Gear?<br>
<br>
Manzana <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=glaekenrasilom>GlaekenRasilom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchanter Realm Member</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#330000>(10/6/03 5:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=321.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LDoN spells worth it?</span><hr size=1>   There is much more to LDoN than just rewards.I have gotten phenominal experiance from level 59 up,experiance which seems FAR surperior to planes considering the amount of time played.At 59 with an entire group of roughly same level toons,it would take me up to 3 hours to see 1 yellow bub of exp in areas like PoD or PoN- however,in LDoN I am seeing the same amount of experiance for a 70 minute session.Lvl 60 was a virtual blur to me as I went from 60 to 61 in 5 sessions in LDoN and still grouped with toons all within a few levels of myself.<br>
<br>
  The drops and rewards for adventure points I view as a plus as the experiance seems to be the best reward one can ask for IMO.It is nice to see augmentable items that are easily on par with items worth up to 100k in bazaar - namely the items that can be augmented and the augments themselves for Flowing Thought.Regen Items are a nice bonus as well and you actually start seeing regen 1 Augs pop up at around 40 points.I have seen Augs that go up to Regen 5 and FT3 so far so Im not sure just how powerful these things get.<br>
<br>
   It is nice to know you can actually purchase without PP an augmentable item and augment that can match and at times far surpass BoFS,all for the price of getting to the next level.Or an Item that might equal Fungal Regrowth basically for free.<br>
  <br>
    As for the spells - well you have to look closely at them and see whether or not you would like them in your spell lineup - clerics have a few that effect incoming melee damage which will be a real hit with tanks - whereas the ones for mages and chanters and such effect incoming magic damage.The problem with casting these spells is that they are not long duration spells,but they definately have thier upsides as you can cause up to 40% incoming spell damage reflect back on caster.Would be a real @#%$ for a wizzie to try and mana burn through this if nearly half the damage came back at him in PVP. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=glaekenrasilom>GlaekenRasilom</A> at: 10/6/03 5:55 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bregaladlow>Bregalad LoW</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchanter Realm Master</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#330000>(10/7/03 11:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=321.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LDoN spells worth it?</span><hr size=1> LDoN experience is surely way better than Tier 1 PoP, but Tier 2 and 3 are still way better - and you can just get in a and grind there, without time constraints.   Not to mention that once you start doing BoT/HoH, you get access to spectrals and runes, which result in far more needed spells.<br>
<br>
LDoN indeed has been good AA exp, and cash is not bad - and since my spell set is complete, (missing only lvl 65 Frog illusion and a couple imbues) I no longer need to work on my PoP spells.  Also, especially Rujarkian dungeons are source of material for easy smithing skillups up to 212.   I am in the post 188 smithing hell, and jump at any chance to skillup.<br>
<br>
Reflect spell indeed looks very nice.  Every 120 seconds, a 12 second period during which you can reflect stuff sounds nice.  If works as advertised, fights vs. massive AoE DD mobs will get interesting.   Alendar...   Might be a useful spell.<br>
<br>
